contenido: La Fundació Ana Ribot selecciona per el Centre de Dia per a gent gran un infermer/a per substitució de BAIXA MATERNAL (8/10 MESOS). L’objectiu del Centre de Dia “Ana Ribot” es potenciar les diferents capacitats físiques, cognitives, socials, emocionals de la persona gran per mantenir-les actives i estimulades. Dins de la nostra filosofía d’innovació en l’atenció a la gent gran, hem posat en marxa una UNITAT D’ALZHEIMER on treballem amb persones en estat moderat i avançat de la malaltia. Els nostres especialistes duen a terme un sistema d’estimulació constant i diari mitjançant diferents tècniques no farmacològiques. La infermera del centre valora les necessitats bàsiques de cada usuari detectant problemes reals i potencials. Elabora, juntament amb la resta de professionals, un pla d’atenció individualitzat, marcant-ne uns objectius i planificant-ne unes activitats o cures necessàries,

We are seeking energetic and motivated sales professionals to join our enterprise account acquisition team. The ideal candidate will have strong new business development experience with a proven track record of selling complex, six to seven figure, technical solutions (information technology or other comparable offerings) to mid to large enterprise clients. As an enterprise acquisition account representative, you will be assigned 5 to 10 enterprise accounts in the Spanish market.
  
Responsibilities 
•Conduct market and customer research to expand commercial insight necessary to build effective customer call plans and sales strategies
•Drive a high volume of high value prospecting and business development activities, to include lead management, needed to reach key decision makers/influencers (technical and business) inside pursuit accounts
•Drive account strategies and coordinate team selling efforts with partners, specialist, management and technical resources necessary to close business.
•Through a rigorous and subject rich training agenda, you will become sale proficient with Hitachi Vantara’s solutions while becoming conversational ready on how Hitachi Vantara delivers business value to its customers and prospects.
•Managing forecast and updating activity plans inside Salesforce




Requirements
•A minimum of 6 years of field sales experience specializing in new logo acquisition and/or new business development.
•An avid hunter with a proven track record of sourcing new leads and leveraging social networking to gain access to decision-makers/influencers necessary to close business.
•Some inside sales or telemarketing experience is a plus.
•Domain knowledge of large enterprise IT environments and corporate buying centers is critical.
•Relationship and sell with experiences with top VARs and Integrators.
•Subject matter expertise in data storage, data management, data analytics and other IT services.
oReq:
•Consistent track record of achieving annual quota targets •Excellent deal management and problem solving skills.
•Develop meaningful account plans. •Strong work ethic and thrives in a fast pace, high growth and matrixed organizational environment.•Desire to learn and acquire new skills and product knowledge.•Must be a proficient user of SalesForce and other MS Office tools.

Condiciones: - Contrato eventual a jornada parcial, de 16 horas semenales, para prestar servicios los fines de semana (viernes y sábado). - Formación a cargo de la empresa. - Convenio colectivo de Minoristas de Alimentación. - Incorporación inmediata.
